<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="24" type="mainText">
Diagnosis: The male is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang" authorityName="Wang" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Draconarius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudulus">D. nudulus Wang</taxonomicName>
<quantity metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.087619999999999" unit="in" value="2003.0">2003 in</quantity>
lacking a patellar apophysis and having a short conductor, but can be distinguished by the short RTA (half or less than half of tibial length), the spoon-shaped median apophysis, and the slightly lobed embolic base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
